antisense_rna.definition: Antisense RNA is RNA that is transcribed from the coding, rather than the template, strand of DNA

guide_rna.label: guide RNA
guide_rna.definition: A short 3'-uridylated RNA that can form a duplex with a stretch of mature edited mRNA

mirna_gene.definition: MicroRNA gene. Predicted using sequences from Rfam and miRBase

misc_rna_gene.label: misc RNA gene
misc_rna_gene.definition: Miscellaneous RNA gene. A non-coding RNA that cannot be classified. Predicted using sequences from Rfam

mt_rrna_gene.label: mt rRNA gene
mt_rrna_gene.definition: Mitochondrially encoded ribosomal RNA gene. Predicted using sequences from Rfam

mt_trna_gene.label: mt tRNA gene
mt_trna_gene.definition: Mitochondrially encoded transfer RNA gene. Predicted using sequences from Rfam

ncrna.label: ncRNA
ncrna.definition: An RNA transcript that does not encode for a protein rather the RNA molecule is the gene product

nontranslating_cds.label: nontranslating CDS
nontranslating_cds.definition: An imported 'protein-coding' gene that does not translate due to one or more unannotated stop codons

pirna_gene.label: piRNA gene
pirna_gene.definition: A gene that encodes for an piwi associated RNA.

polymorphic_pseudogene.label: polymorphic pseudogene
polymorphic_pseudogene.definition: Pseudogene that is disrupted in the reference genome but present as an intact protein-coding gene in other haplotypes

pre_mirna.label: pre miRNA
pre_mirna.definition: The 60-70 nt region remain after Drosha processing of the primary transcript, that folds back upon itself to form a hairpin structure

processed_pseudogene.label: processed pseudogene
processed_pseudogene.definition: Pseudogene derived via retrotransposition of the mRNA from a functional protein-coding gene

protein_coding_gene.label: protein coding gene
protein_coding_gene.definition: Gene that is known or predicted to encode a stable and/or functional protein

pseudogene.label: pseudogene
pseudogene.definition: Locus derived from a protein-coding gene containing disabling mutations or truncations and believed to not encode a stable and or functional protein

ribozyme_gene.label: ribozyme gene
ribozyme_gene.definition: Ribozyme gene. An RNA enzyme that catalyzes a chemical reaction. Predicted using sequences from Rfam

rna_subunit_of_the_rnase.label: RNA subunit of the RNase
rna_subunit_of_the_rnase.definition: RNA subunit of the RNase mitochondrial RNA processing (MRP)

rnase_p_rna.label: RNase P RNA
rnase_p_rna.definition: The RNA component of endoribonuclease Ribonuclease P found in archaea, bacteria and eukarya as well as chloroplasts and mitochondria

rrna_gene.label: rRNA gene
rrna_gene.definition: Ribosomal RNA gene. Predicted using sequences from Rfam

rrna_pseudogene.label: rRNA pseudogene

scarna_gene.label: scaRNA gene

sense_intronic_gene.label: sense intronic gene
sense_intronic_gene.definition: Long non-coding RNA gene contained within introns of a coding gene but does not overlap any exons

sense_overlapping_gene.label: sense overlapping gene
sense_overlapping_gene.definition: Long non-coding RNA gene that contains a coding gene in one of its introns on the same strand

snorna_gene.label: snoRNA gene
snorna_gene.definition: Small nucleolar RNA.gene. Predicted using sequences from Rfam

snrna_gene.label: snRNA gene

srna_gene.label: sRNA gene

translated_processed_pseudogene.definition: Processed pseudogene with experimental evidence of translation

translated_unprocessed_pseudogene.label: translated unprocessed pseudogene
translated_unprocessed_pseudogene.definition: Unprocessed pseudogene with experiemental evidence of translation

transposable_element.label: transposable element
transposable_element.definition: A transposon or insertion sequence. An element that can insert in a variety of DNA sequences

trna_gene.label: tRNA gene
trna_gene.definition: A noncoding RNA that binds to a specific amino acid to allow that amino acid to be used by the ribosome during translation of RNA

trna_pseudogene.label: tRNA pseudogene
trna_pseudogene.definition: Noncoding descendant of a tRNA, part of a pseudogene

unitary_pseudogene.label: unitary pseudogene
unitary_pseudogene.definition: Non-functional copy of an ancestral functional protein-coding gene

unprocessed_pseudogene.label: unprocessed pseudogene
unprocessed_pseudogene.definition: Pseudogene derived via complete or partial duplication of a functional protein-coding gene

vault_rna_gene.label: vault RNA gene
